Produce forest plots to visualize covariate effects using either the command line or an interactive 'Shiny' application.

name: r-coveffectsplot
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.0.9' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-coveffectsplot
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/coveffectsplot_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/coveffectsplot/coveffectsplot_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 960176cc5620b40168136e33d7bcbcd14521aaa42e5ad6ce78eeb98a9dc8e7db

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-colourpicker
    - r-data.table
    - r-dplyr
    - r-egg
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-ggstance
    - r-markdown
    - r-shiny
    - r-shinyjs
    - r-table1
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-colourpicker
    - r-data.table
    - r-dplyr
    - r-egg
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-ggstance
    - r-markdown
    - r-shiny
    - r-shinyjs
    - r-table1
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('coveffectsplot')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('coveffectsplot')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/smouksassi/interactiveforestplot
  license: MIT
  summary: Produce forest plots to visualize covariate effects using either the command line
    or an interactive 'Shiny' application.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
